## Instance Assignment Strategy

### Standard Instance Allocation

| Instance ID | Worktree | Branch | Port | Primary Role |
|-------------|----------|--------|------|--------------|
| `claude-main` | main | main | 3000 | Production testing, critical fixes |
| `claude-feature` | feature-slot-edit | feature/slot-edit | 3001 | Feature development |
| `claude-fix` | fix-sign-out-issues | fix/sign-out-issues | 3002 | Bug fixes |
| `claude-dev` | dev | main | 3003 | Experimentation, testing |
| `claude-test` | test | main | 3004 | E2E testing, QA |
| `claude-docs` | docs | main | 3005 | Documentation updates |

### Dynamic Instance Creation

For new tasks not fitting the standard allocation:

```bash
# Create new worktree for instance
./create-instance-worktree.sh <instance-id> <branch-name> <port>

# Example:
./create-instance-worktree.sh claude-ui feature/ui-redesign 3006
```

This creates:
- Worktree at `parkboard-worktrees/<instance-id>/`
- Lock file at `parkboard-worktrees/.locks/<instance-id>.lock`
- Scratchpad at `parkboard-worktrees/.scratchpads/<instance-id>.md`

