## Automated Coordination

### Status Monitor Script

Create `parkboard-worktrees/monitor.sh`:

```bash
#!/bin/bash
# Continuous monitoring of all instances

watch -n 10 '
echo "=== PARKBOARD INSTANCE STATUS ==="
echo ""
for scratchpad in parkboard-worktrees/.scratchpads/*.md; do
  instance=$(basename "$scratchpad" .md)
  status=$(grep "State:" "$scratchpad" | cut -d" " -f2)
  task=$(grep "Working On:" "$scratchpad" | cut -d":" -f2-)
  echo "[$status] $instance: $task"
done
echo ""
echo "=== ACTIVE LOCKS ==="
ls -1 parkboard-worktrees/.locks/*.lock 2>/dev/null | xargs -I{} basename {} .lock
echo ""
echo "=== PORT STATUS ==="
for port in 3000 3001 3002 3003 3004 3005; do
  if lsof -ti:$port >/dev/null 2>&1; then
    echo "Port $port: BUSY"
  else
    echo "Port $port: FREE"
  fi
done
'
```

### Conflict Checker Script

