## Instance Initialization Checklist

When a new Claude instance starts work:

### Phase 1: Environment Setup (2 minutes)

- [ ] Identify your instance ID (e.g., `claude-feature`)
- [ ] Navigate to your assigned worktree
  ```bash
  cd /home/ltpt420/repos/parkboard-worktrees/<your-worktree>
  ```
- [ ] Verify dependencies are installed
  ```bash
  npm list 2>&1 | head -5
  ```
- [ ] Check your assigned port is free
  ```bash
  lsof -ti:<your-port> || echo "Port is free"
  ```

### Phase 2: Coordination Setup (3 minutes)

- [ ] Read ALL instance scratchpads
  ```bash
  cat /home/ltpt420/repos/parkboard-worktrees/.scratchpads/*.md
  ```
- [ ] Read shared scratchpad for alerts
  ```bash
  cat /home/ltpt420/repos/parkboard-worktrees/.scratchpads/shared.md
  ```
- [ ] Check for active locks
  ```bash
  ls -la /home/ltpt420/repos/parkboard-worktrees/.locks/
  ```
- [ ] Review task board
  ```bash
  cat /home/ltpt420/repos/parkboard-worktrees/.coordination/task-board.md
  ```

### Phase 3: Status Announcement (2 minutes)

- [ ] Update your scratchpad with current status
- [ ] Set state to WORKING
- [ ] List files you'll be editing
- [ ] Announce task in shared scratchpad
- [ ] Acquire locks if needed

### Phase 4: Start Work (ongoing)

- [ ] Start dev server on assigned port
- [ ] Update scratchpad every 15 minutes
- [ ] Check for urgent messages every 5 minutes
- [ ] Commit frequently with descriptive messages
- [ ] Update task board as you progress

### Phase 5: Completion (5 minutes)

- [ ] Run tests
  ```bash
  npm test
  ```
- [ ] Update scratchpad to COMPLETED
- [ ] Release all locks
- [ ] Commit and push changes
- [ ] Update task board
- [ ] Move completed task to DONE

